name: Ride Till I Die - hybrid camber
description:
Ride Till I Die is the board that will ride as hard as you do. This board will take your soul for a ride of excessive pleasures that your parents warned you about. If Satan, the dark lord was real he would ride this board, it's just that evil...

The hybrid camber has the profile of camber between your feet for added control and precision but outside of your feet the board has a reverse camber profile aka rocker. This combination of camber and rocker allows you to have the power and precision of camber but allows you the comfort and forgiveness of a rocker.

This board has HPPE sidewalls, HPPE is an extremely tough material because of its high molecular weight. It also has the highest impact strength of any thermoplastic presently made. Science aside these sidewalls are built tough so you can slay all types of terrain.
 
Our bases are ISO 7200 Sintered bases, they are fast and durable. They are built for performance with a low coefficient of friction they glide better than extruded bases to help keep you hopping and waddling your way out of the flats.
 
This board is a true twin meaning the center to tip and the center to the tail have identical dimensions. This allows you to ride, land or take off switch the same as your normal stance.
 
We use environmentally friendly epoxy, Super Sap is a performance grade eco-resin. This eco-resin improves adhesion and elasticity between materials and also helps us reduce environmental impacts that go along with manufacturing snowboards. This way you can help protect the mountains and environment that we love and rely on.
 
The cores are made using select grade poplar which has great bending and stiffness properties that are ideal for making snowboards. The cores are constructed with full length stringers to provide you with a board with even stiffness throughout and eliminates stress risers caused by using finger joints.
 
Triaxle fiberglass is used to provide your board with better torsion strength and stiffness than biaxial, this translates to better edge control and stability while you ride.

name: Eternal - camber
description:
The Eternal is for the traditional riders. This is the camber you grew up with the timeless profile will be classic for eternity. Worship this board like you were in Sunday school, this board will lift your soul as you shred the park with power and precision. Amen.

Camber is the tradition snowboard profile, it is raised up slightly between the tip and tail. When you stand on the board it becomes loaded like a spring ready to pop. These boards provide you with the power and precision to shred the park in all its glory.

name: Gas Mask - Zero Camber
description:
Be ready for war with the Gas Mask. This board will have you breathing easy whether your riding through powder, groomers or the park.

Zero camber is flat between the tip and tail of the snowboard. This will give you a more forgiving ride than camber. Zero camber also make it easier for you to do presses, butters and float on powder. This board is perfect for you if you like to shred all types of terrain.

name: Zombie Apocalypse - Reverse Camber
description:
This board mixes in our heritage by using profiles inspired by the early board sports like surfing and skating. This is the weapon of choice for slaying zombies and killin' it in the park.

Reverse camber aka rocker is the opposite of camber. The center dips down slightly and curves up towards the tip and tail. This creates a ride more like a surfboard or skateboard. It allows you to effortlessly do ollies, presses and float on powder.
